sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Dashboard
    participant C as Controller
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant A as Agent
    participant Disp as Dispatcher

    Note over D,C: 1. Remove Request
    D->>C: DashboardRemoveAgentMessage<br/>(agent_id)
    C->>DB: SELECT agent (FOR UPDATE)<br/>row-level lock

    Note over C,A: 2. Disconnect Agent
    C->>A: DisconnectMessage<br/>(reason: "Removed by controller")
    C->>A: WebSocket close (code 1000)
    C->>C: Remove from agent_connections

    Note over C,DB: 3. Re-queue Active Jobs
    C->>DB: SELECT jobs assigned to agent
    alt Job is ASSIGNED or RUNNING
        C->>DB: job.status → QUEUED<br/>clear assigned_agent_id<br/>clear started_at
    else Job is COMPLETED / PASSED / FAILED
        C->>DB: clear assigned_agent_id only
    end

    Note over C,DB: 4. Delete Agent
    C->>DB: DELETE AgentRecord
    C->>DB: COMMIT

    Note over C,Disp: 5. Redispatch
    C->>Disp: try_dispatch()
    Disp->>DB: Find queued jobs +<br/>available online agents
    opt Re-queued job matched
        Disp->>DB: job → ASSIGNED<br/>new agent → BUSY
        Disp-->>A: JobAssignMessage to new agent
    end

    Note over D: 6. Dashboard Notification
    C-->>D: DashboardSnapshotMessage<br/>(agent removed, jobs updated)
